# **ğŸ“„ButtonLeaderboard**

## **ğŸ§© Description**

ButtonLeaderboard is an interactive button that displays a translated title (â€œleaderboardâ€) and a dynamic state icon (an upward or downward arrow) depending on whether the leaderboard is currently visible. It also shows a fixed numerical progress (2536 / 20000).

---

## **âœ…Props**

| **Name** | **Type** | **Required** | **Description** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| onClick | function | âœ… | Function called when the button is clicked |
| showLeaderboard | boolean | âœ… | Determines whether the leaderboard is currently shown, to toggle the icon |

---

## **ğŸŒInternationalization**

- The component uses the **language context** via useLang() from LangProvider.
- It retrieves the translation for "leaderboard" from the TranslationsDictionary.

```
<p>{TranslationsDictionary[selectedLang]?.["leaderboard"]}</p>
```

---

## **ğŸ¨Visual Behavior**

- **Size**: 300px x 40px
- **Background**: white by default, turns black on hover (hover:bg-black)
- **Text**: purple #5328EA, bold (font-[600]), custom font font-Gotham
- **Border**: 2px thick, purple #5328EA, rounded corners 12px
- **Layout**:
    - Horizontal flex layout with space-between
    - Icon on the left (ChevronUpIcon or ChevronDownIcon)
    - Centered label
    - Fixed progress value "2536 / 20000" on the right

---

## **ğŸ–¼Icons Used**

- ChevronUpIcon / ChevronDownIcon from lucide-react
    - Displayed based on the showLeaderboard state

---

## **ğŸ’¡Example Usage**

```
<ButtonLeaderboard
  onClick={() => setShowLeaderboard(prev => !prev)}
  showLeaderboard={showLeaderboard}
/>
```

---

## **ğŸ› Dependencies**

- React
- lucide-react for icons
- useLang and TranslationsDictionary for language support

---

## **ğŸ“¦Export**

